M|references|**Percentage of sale:**
M|references|- Standard: 10-30% of first sale or first year
M|references|- Works for: E-commerce, SaaS with clear pricing
M|references|- Example: "Earn 25% of every sale you refer"
M|references|**Flat fee per action:**
M|references|- Standard: $5-500 depending on value
M|references|- Works for: Lead gen, trials, freemium
M|references|- Example: "$50 for every qualified demo"
M|references|**Recurring commission:**
M|references|- Standard: 10-25% of recurring revenue
M|references|- Works for: Subscription products
M|references|- Example: "20% of subscription for 12 months"
M|references|**Tiered commission:**
M|references|- Works for: Motivating high performers
M|references|- Example: "20% for 1-10 sales, 25% for 11-25, 30% for 26+"
M|references|How long after click does affiliate get credit?
M|references|| Duration | Use Case |
M|references||----------|----------|
M|references|| 24 hours | High-volume, low-consideration purchases |
M|references|| 7-14 days | Standard e-commerce |
M|references|| 30 days | Standard SaaS/B2B |
M|references|| 60-90 days | Long sales cycles, enterprise |
M|references|| Lifetime | Premium affiliate relationships |
